title: Inlet with Rocky Cliffs and Fisherman
provenance: Anna Richards Brewster, Scarsdale, NY, 1905-1952; William T. Brewster,
medium: Pen and black ink on off-white wove paper
description: Rocky coastline surrpunding an inlet. A small figure carrying what is probably a fishing pole is in the left-middle gound at edge of water, There are large cliffs in the distance, at right. Miscellaneous pen strokes in the margin to the right of the image.
